body:
When calling `circt-opt --lower-loopschedule-to-calyx ./test.mlir`,  `circt-opt` fail due to 
```
circt-opt: /home/kelvin/circt/llvm/mlir/lib/IR/PatternMatch.cpp:182: auto mlir::RewriterBase::eraseOp(mlir::Operation *)::(anonymous class)::operator()(mlir::Operation *) const: Assertion `mayBeGraphRegion(*op->getParentRegion()) && "expected that op has no uses"' failed.
```

test.mlir:
```mlir
module {
  func.func @foo(%arg0: i32) attributes {} {
    %const = arith.constant 1 : index
    loopschedule.pipeline II =  2 trip_count =  20 iter_args(%counter = %const) : (index) -> () {
      %latch = arith.cmpi ult, %counter, %const : index
      loopschedule.register %latch : i1
    } do {
      %stage0:2 = loopschedule.pipeline.stage start = 0 {
        %op = arith.addi %counter, %const : index
        %count = arith.addi %counter, %const : index
        loopschedule.register %op, %count : index, index
      } : index, index
      %stage1 = loopschedule.pipeline.stage start = 1 {
        loopschedule.register %stage0#0: index
      } : index
      %stage3 = loopschedule.pipeline.stage start = 7 {
        %moreOp = arith.addi %stage1, %const : index
        loopschedule.register %moreOp : index
      } : index
      loopschedule.terminator iter_args(%stage0#1), results() : (index) -> ()
    }
    return
  }
}
```

I have spent some time looking at what led to this, and it seems like the `%stage1` value is leading to the problem.

